The paper deals with a graph problem related to network propagation and social networks, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The problem also involves threshold values and approximation algorithms, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions the use of FPT (Fixed Parameter Tractability) and hardness results, which could indicate a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
